sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as "AI Platform"
    participant Transport as "StreamableHTTPServerTransport<br/>/mcp"
    participant SessionMgr as "sessions Map"
    participant EventStore as "InMemoryEventStore"
    participant MCP as "MCP Server"
    participant AutoMem as "AutoMemClient"
    
    Note over Client,AutoMem: Session Initialization
    Client->>Transport: POST /mcp<br/>isInitializeRequest(body)
    Transport->>SessionMgr: sessionIdGenerator()
    SessionMgr-->>Transport: sessionId (UUID)
    Transport->>EventStore: create stream
    Transport->>SessionMgr: set(sessionId, {transport, server, type})
    Transport->>MCP: connect(transport)
    Transport-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>Mcp-Session-Id: {sessionId}
    
    Note over Client,AutoMem: Tool Invocation
    Client->>Transport: POST /mcp<br/>Mcp-Session-Id: {sessionId}<br/>tool: recall_memory
    Transport->>SessionMgr: get(sessionId)
    SessionMgr-->>Transport: {transport, server}
    Transport->>MCP: CallToolRequestSchema
    MCP->>AutoMem: recallMemory(args)
    AutoMem-->>MCP: {results: [...]}
    MCP-->>Transport: JSON-RPC response
    Transport->>EventStore: storeEvent(sessionId, message)
    Transport-->>Client: SSE event + JSON-RPC result
    
    Note over Client,AutoMem: Resumability (connection drop)
    Client->>Transport: GET /mcp<br/>Mcp-Session-Id: {sessionId}<br/>Last-Event-ID: {lastId}
    Transport->>EventStore: replayEventsAfter(sessionId, lastId)
    EventStore-->>Transport: missed events
    Transport-->>Client: SSE stream with replayed events
    
    Note over Client,AutoMem: Session Cleanup
    Transport->>SessionMgr: check lastAccess timestamp
    SessionMgr->>SessionMgr: delete if > 1 hour idle
    SessionMgr->>EventStore: removeStream(sessionId)